### Description

I have got this part of code where I have declared and initialized my formgroup. If there is passed down Input() party, I want to delete "politicians" formArray:

```
  @Input() party: IPoliticalParty | null;

  public partyForm = this._fb.group({
    name: this._fb.nonNullable.control('', { validators: Validators.required }),
    image: this._fb.nonNullable.control('', Validators.required),
    tags: this._fb.nonNullable.control('', Validators.required),
    politicians: this._fb.array([]),
  });

  constructor(private _fb: FormBuilder) {
    super();
  }

  ngOnInit(): void {
    if (this.party) {
      this.partyForm.removeControl('politicians'); //Error - No overload matches this call
    }
  }
```

However, when I try to removeControl, I get error mentioned in error section bellow.
I have tried to initialize formgroup without formArray control, however is is not the issue. Also tried to remove other control but problem still occures. It must be issue with typed formgroup.

Only what helped me was to cast partyForm to FormGroup, so it looks like this now:
```
  @Input() party: IPoliticalParty | null;

  public partyForm = this._fb.group({
    name: this._fb.nonNullable.control('', { validators: Validators.required }),
    image: this._fb.nonNullable.control('', Validators.required),
    tags: this._fb.nonNullable.control('', Validators.required),
    politicians: this._fb.array([]),
  });

  constructor(private _fb: FormBuilder) {
    super();
  }

  ngOnInit(): void {
    if (this.party) {
    //Cast to FormGroup
      (<FormGroup>this.partyForm).removeControl('politicians');
    }
  }
```
It looks like there is issue between strictly typed forms and removeControl(), if I modify initialization of formGroup like this, now formGroup is of type FormGroup any and error doesn't occure.

```
  @Input() party: IPoliticalParty | null;

// I say that partyForm is FormGroup, but then I lost my typed form and partyForm is type FormGroup<any>.
  public partyForm: FormGroup = this._fb.group({
    name: this._fb.nonNullable.control('', { validators: Validators.required }),
    image: this._fb.nonNullable.control('', Validators.required),
    tags: this._fb.nonNullable.control('', Validators.required),
    politicians: this._fb.array([]),
  });

  constructor(private _fb: FormBuilder) {
    super();
  }

  ngOnInit(): void {
    if (this.party) {
      this.partyForm.removeControl('politicians');
    }
  }
```




