### Description

Hello,
We are implementing a micro frontend application using @angular/elements. The method for waiting for Angular testabilities to be stable that we use in our test solution, does not catch instabilities in the testabilities of the micro app that is called from the main application.
We tried emitting tetabilities from micro app and registered them in the main app, but it didn't work.
Please let us know if there is a way already, or accept that as a feature request.

### Proposed solution

Testabilities of the micro application to be registered automatically.

### Alternatives considered

Here is how we tried registering testabilities:
micro app:
```
@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  templateUrl: './app.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./app.component.scss']
})
export class AppComponent implements OnInit {
  @Output() testability: EventEmitter<any> = new EventEmitter<any>(); 

  ngOnInit() {
    this.router.initialNavigation();
    this.testability.emit(window.getAllAngularTestabilities()[0]);
  }
}
```

main app html:
```
<micro-app (testability)="onTestability($event)"</micro-app>
```
main app ts:
```
@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  templateUrl: './app.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./app.component.scss']
})
export class AppComponent {
  constructor( private testRegistry: TestabilityRegistry) {  }

  onTestability(event: any): void {
    let microApp= document.getElementsByTagName('micro-app');
    this.testRegistry.registerApplication(microApp, event?.detail);
  }
}

### Feature Description

There should be a built in feature to in select dropdown in angular material to select and deselect all option in dropdown. Currently we have to custom code this feature using mat-select-trigger like below code.

### Use Case

### Feature Description

There should be a built in feature to in select dropdown in angular material to select and deselect all option in dropdown. Currently we have to custom code this feature using mat-select-trigger like below code. 

### Use Case

There are numerous example where this feature is needed. This is quite a general feature which is needed most of the time in case of multiple selection. For example like below code, we can have multiple boarding option for user accounts app for admin, if he want to select all option, he needed to select all one by one, base on which our api is called. If some cases option are so much that its hard and time consuming to select or deselect all of them.
Currently there a lot of extra line of code need to be implemented to have this feature, and in some sites there can be lot of dropdowns especially in CMS sites. Built in feature for this save a lot of extra effort for this.

**Html File**
```
<mat-form-field class="ml-lg-auto mr-2 width-200">
                      <mat-select placeholder="Filter by Onboarding State"   [(ngModel)]="selectedOnboardingStates"
                           [compareWith]="compareSelectOptions" multiple >
                      <mat-select-trigger>
                        <mat-label *ngIf="selectedOnboardingStates && onBoardingStates.length !== 1 && 
                                     selectedOnboardingStates.length === onBoardingStates.length">All</mat-label>
                        <ng-container *ngIf="selectedOnboardingStates && selectedOnboardingStates.length !== 
                           onBoardingStates.length">{{selectedOnboardingStates[0] ? selectedOnboardingStates[0].name : ''}}<span *ngIf="selectedOnboardingStates.length > 1" class="example-additional-selection">
                            (+{{selectedOnboardingStates.length - 1}} {{selectedOnboardingStates.length === 2 ? 'other' : 'others'}})
                          </span>
                        </ng-container>
                      </mat-select-trigger> 
                      
                      <div class="mat-option" *ngIf="onBoardingStates && onBoardingStates.length !== 1">
                        <mat-checkbox color="primary" (change)="$event ? masterToggle() : null"
                          [indeterminate]="isAnySelected() && !isAllSelected()" [formControl]="masterToggleCheckbox"
                          class="qa-checkbox-master"
